# Frontend Conventions (apps/web/)

## Stack
- React 18 + TypeScript 5.5 + Vite (SWC)
- Styling: Tailwind CSS v4 + shadcn/ui (Radix UI)
- State: React Query (TanStack Query v5) for server state, React Context for global state
- Forms: react-hook-form + Zod validation
- Auth: Auth0 via Supabase third-party auth
- Charts: D3.js + Recharts
- Animations: Framer Motion
- Icons: Lucide React

## Key Conventions

### Imports
- ALWAYS use `@/` path alias (resolves to `src/`). Never relative imports.
- Use barrel exports from `index.ts` files for shared modules.
- Example: `import { useDebounce } from "@/hooks/shared"`

### Components
- Functional components with hooks only (no class components)
- Use shadcn/ui primitives from `@/components/ui/` for all standard UI elements
- PascalCase file names (e.g., `HelpDrawer.tsx`, `FinancialTableCell.tsx`)
- Props typed as interfaces: `interface ComponentNameProps { ... }`
- Follow pattern in `apps/web/src/components/ui/button.tsx` for CVA variants

### Styling
- Tailwind utility classes via `cn()` from `@/lib/utils` for conditional classes
- No CSS modules, no styled-components, no inline styles
- Custom theme variables defined in `src/index.css` (CSS custom properties)
- Use `tailwindcss-animate` plugin classes for animations

### State Management
- Server state: React Query `useQuery()` / `useMutation()` — never raw fetch
- Global state: React Context API (auth, module contexts)
- Local state: `useState` for UI state only
- Follow pattern in `apps/web/src/contexts/auth/AuthContext.tsx`

### Data Fetching
- Supabase client from `@/integrations/supabase/client`
- Service classes with static methods (e.g., `InputDataService.loadInputs()`)
- Error handling: try-catch with toast notifications (sonner)
- Follow pattern in `apps/web/src/services/InputDataService.ts`

### Forms
- react-hook-form with shadcn/ui Form wrapper components
- Zod schemas for validation
- Follow pattern in `apps/web/src/components/ui/form.tsx`

### Routing
- React Router v6 with nested routes
- Protected routes via `ProtectedRoute` wrapper component
- Programmatic navigation via `useNavigate()` hook

### Naming
- Components/Types: PascalCase
- Hooks: camelCase with `use` prefix
- Utils/services: camelCase
- Directories: kebab-case for feature folders (e.g., `return-distribution/`)
- Types: `interface` for object shapes, `type` for unions and aliases

### File Organization
- `components/ui/` — shadcn/ui primitives
- `components/shared/` — Cross-module components
- `components/{module}/` — Feature-specific components
- `hooks/{module}/` — Feature-specific hooks
- `contexts/{module}/` — Feature-specific contexts
- `services/` — API service classes
- `types/` — TypeScript type definitions

## Anti-Patterns
- Do NOT use relative imports — always `@/` alias
- Do NOT use Redux, Zustand, or MobX — use React Query + Context
- Do NOT use MUI, Ant Design, or Chakra — use shadcn/ui + Radix
- Do NOT use CSS modules or styled-components — use Tailwind
- Do NOT use `any` type — prefer proper typing
- Do NOT add new UI dependencies without checking shadcn/ui first
